||===========================================================||
|| My STM32 NUCLEO-G071RB (ARM Cortex-M0+) Learning progress ||
||===========================================================||

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

REQUIREMENTS
============

* arm-none-eabi-gcc (Compiler)
* make (Build System)
* openOCD
* GDB (for ARM processors, I used `gdb-multiarch`)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

BUILDING AND UPLOADING
======================

To Build, go into one of the folders and run
```
make
```

To build as well as flash(upload) the program after that, then run
```
make flash
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ORGANIZATION
============

Organization of the folders are in such a way that each folder is self-complete,
and no need for extra things other than the requirements mentioned above. List
of the folders with their brief description:

01. Made a LED Blink, enable clock for GPIOA, then set the MODE of Pin5 of GPIOA
    to output-mode, and then setting and clearing the corresponding bit in the
    OUTPUT Register of GPIOA after some delay.

